&quot;Ask Al Jazeera what they think of the free speech on the internet.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Ironic isn't it....(with the Arab countries being the great bastions of Freedom they are and all).<br>
<br>
The fact is...for every quasi-vigilante act of &quot;counter-free-speech&quot; which you can point out on the Internet, my dog (though admittedly, he is very smart) could easily locate 1000 examples of unobstructed social/political/artistic/scientific information-sharing between people which would not have been there even a few years ago.<br>
<br>
The ability to locate and share thoughts, music, art, programs...with people who do not even speak you language almost instantly seems a pretty big boon for the whole &quot;free speech&quot; thing....then again, perhaps I'm wrong here?....<br>
